title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta Stampede 45LC - With Professional Action Work
postcontent:
I have a Beretta Stampede for sale. It's a single action revolver, and a real throwback to the old west. It's a replica of the legendary Colt Single Action Army 1873. Also known as the "Peacemaker". It's chambered in 45 Colt, which is a lot more authentic than similar guns chambered in .357. The Peacemaker was originally offered in 45 Colt, and that's why I have enjoyed shooting this gun so much. 

A while back I wanted to get her a tune up so I sent it off to Long Hunter for some professional action work: (http://www.longhunt.com/gunsmithing/colt.htm). Long Hunter is one of the premier gunsmith operations for working on old west firearms. They did a beautiful job with my Beretta. Turned it from a good shooter to a great one! 

This Stampede is antiqued as you can see, and looks like a relic of the old west. It's configured in a 4 3/4'' barrel, also known as the "Gunslinger" model. You're sure to love this piece as much as I do. It's rugged, tough, and will hold up to a lifetime of shooting. 

So why am I selling it? Well, I've decided to build a collection of Cowboy action firearms and I want everything to match. I got a new Single Action Army that looks similar to my levergun so I decided I may as well part with my Beretta. If interested, just contact me. I'm willing to negotiate on the cost, and I'd be happy to talk trade as well. I'd add or subtract cash for the right trade. So let me know!

title: For Sale:  Everey Gun on the Market!
postcontent:
ARMSLIST and all other gun marketplaces are community run for the most part. As a gun community we need to come together to rid ourselves of one of the deadliest sins - GREED. We are all tired of seeing $500 AK-47s listed at $2000, and $800 fully upgraded AR-15s posted for $4500. 

Guess what? As gun buyers and members on this and other forums, we are just as responsible for the state of our society as the price gougers and hoarders are. We need to come together and do two things: 
(1) STOP BUYING AT THESE RIDICULOUS PRICES and 
(2) click on the ad, go to "Flag" at the top, and press "overpriced." This whole process takes 1.3968 seconds.

These price CRIMINALS only have business if someone is ignorant enough to buy and if they spread their advertisement. NOTE TO GUN COMMUNITY: Guns aren't going anywhere. Ammo isn't going anywhere. Magazines are the biggest threat of changing, BUT YOU CAN ORDER 20 RIGHT NOW THROUGH OPERATION BOULDER AIRLIFT ON MAGPUL'S FACEBOOK.

Every time you skip over a $10,000 ad for a $3000 purchased SCAR 17, you have just became part of the problem. Send them a hate email showing the prices before hoarding and then promptly FLAG their ad so we can get prices back where they belong. For the uninformed or misinformed audience, I have put together a short list of reasonable prices for standard guns. What I am asking is that everyone read this post and then immediately copy and paste it to another state's/towns listing in the US. Add your own two cents in if you'd like. The regularity will only return if we make it.

AR-15: $700-$1300 depending on brand and usage (shots fired, wear, etc..)
AK-47: $400-$900
SKS:$300-$500
SCAR 16/17: $2000/$2800
AR-10: $1000-1500 (tops)
Glock: $400-600
10/22: $229 (you can buy these at Wal-Mart)
ACR: $2000
1911: $600-1100

Ammo:
9mm ammo: $0.25/round is on the higher end
223/5.56: $0.35/round
.308/7.62 NATO: maybe up to $1/round (on high side)
.22: $0.05/round is high

Again, feel free to add your $0.02, make changes, repost, and then get to the flagging of overpriced scams.

postcontent:
Hello,

I have 100 rounds of Brass cased Sadu 5.56 (basically M855) steel core penetrating rounds. This is awesome shooting ammo. If you have a capable gun and have only shot 223, you will enjoy the extra pop of 5.56. This ammo has a sealed primer and bullet crimp, so if you chose, you can store for probably decades if thats your thing.

I would like to trade for 9mm, but would consider .22lr and/or .45 auto as well. Please shoot me an email with what you would like to trade. Unfortunately ammo has been going crazy, and I'd like to trade with someone who maybe stocked up on 9mm when times were better so we can both enjoy the sport during this climate.

I hate to feed into the hype, but this is probably the type of ammo that would be the first on the list to be banned or highly regulated if it came to that...I'm not saying I expect that to happen, but its something to think about.
